# README #

hxTool is a standalone tool that can be used with FireEye HX endpoint technology. hxTool provides additional features not directly available in the product.

### What is this repository for? ###

* Summary
hxTool is a web based application that allows users to utilize functionality in the FireEye HX API

* Version
2.0

### How do I get set up? ###

* Summary of set up
To install hxTool unzip or fetch the repo and place the files in a directory. Make sure you have Python 2.7 and the python-flask library installed. After installation run "python hxtool.py" and the server will start listening to tcp port 8080. Access the web user interface via a browser (tested with google chrome and firefox)

* Configuration
None yet

* Dependencies
Python 2.7
Python Flask library

